.TH "BSON_SNPRINTF" "3" "2016\(hy02\(hy04" "libbson"
.SH NAME
bson_snprintf() \- This is a portable wrapper around snprintf(). It also enforces a trailing \0 in the resulting string.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
int
bson_snprintf (char       *str,
               size_t      size,
               const char *format,
               ...) BSON_GNUC_PRINTF (3, 4);
.fi
.fi

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B
.B str
The destination buffer.
.LP
.TP
.B
.B size
The size of
.B str
\e&.
.LP
.TP
.B
.B format
A printf style format string.
.LP

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

This is a portable wrapper around
.B snprintf(3)
\e&. It also enforces a trailing
.B \e0
in the resulting string.

.SH "RETURNS"

The number of bytes written to
.B str
\e&.


.B
